Linearly dependantA vector r is said to be linear combination of a,b,c and so on. If it can be expressed linearly in terms of a,b,c and so on. r=xa+yb+zc+....e.g. r=3i+4jr is written as the sum of i and j Note: When it is said that a,b and c are linearly dependant vectors that means only one of the vectors can be written as the sum of the other two. i.e. c=xa+yb Coplanar ⟹Linearly dependant a,b and c are coplanar and thus are linearly dependant.
Linearly Independant v1,v2,v3.....and so on are said to be linearly independant if 𝜆1v1+𝜆2v2+....+𝜆nvn=0𝜆1=𝜆2=𝜆3=........=𝜆n=0 Two non-collinear vectors are linearly independant. Non-Coplanar⟹Linearly independant
